18/04/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Deputy Foreign Minister Yiannis Valinakis and Finnish counterpart Antti Peltomaki met in Athens on Monday (17 April) to discuss the EU enlargement process and Finland's upcoming presidency of the bloc. His office says Valinakis reaffirmed Greek support for the EU accession prospects of Turkey and countries of the Western Balkans, while stressing the importance of meeting Union membership criteria. Finland is due to assume the rotating EU presidency from Austria in July. (ANA, MPA - 17/04/06)
